OL,3,CFraudster who conned couple out of
OL,4,C#170,000 jailed
OL,6,FThe offences were committed in October
OL,7,F2020, several weeks after the victims
OL,8,Fhad received a fraudulent email which
OL,9,Fthey believed had been sent by the
OL,10,Fsame organisation they were
OL,11,Fconsidering investing in.
OL,13,FIt was one year after transferring the
OL,14,Fmoney that they realised they had been
OL,15,Ftricked, as the telephone numbers they
OL,16,Fhad previously been provided with no
OL,17,Flonger worked.
OL,19,FThey had wanted to reinvest the funds
OL,20,Felsewhere but were instead left empty-
OL,21,Fhanded.
